Package fun.connor.fantasy.Athlete

Class Athlete

  • java.lang.Object
    • fun.connor.fantasy.Athlete.Athlete
  • public class Athlete
extends java.lang.Object
    The Athlete class holds all relevant information for a draftable athlete. There is a single object for all athlete types. Different types manifest in different statistics modules that can be changed at runtime.

      • Athlete

        public Athlete​(java.util.UUID athleteID,
               AthleteName athleteName,
               AthleteType athleteType,
               AthleteStatistics athleteStatistics)
        The base constructor for the athlete. The statistics module is the only attribute that can be changed with a setter.
        Parameters:
        athleteID - The ID assigned to the athlete
        athleteName - The AthleteName object representing the athlete's name
        athleteType - The type of athlete. i.e. the sport the athlete plays
        athleteStatistics - The statistics module for the athlete. This should correspond with its type
